                <head>351. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 18, <persName corresp="#p_WLGST1">General Williams</persName>
                    forwarded to <persName corresp="#p_SAFB1">Admiral Stump</persName> a 15-page
                    summary of <gloss target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_TERM1"
                        >TERM</gloss> activities for the period from November 1955 to November 1956.
                    Copies went also to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_RGF1">Reinhardt</persName>
                    and <persName corresp="#p_TGMD1">General Maxwell D. Taylor</persName>, Chief of
                    Staff, United States Army. (Center of Military History, <persName
                        corresp="#p_WLGST1">Williams</persName> Papers, Official Correspondence 1956
                    (8)) A “Terms of Reference for the U.S. Military Assistance Advisory Group to
                    Vietnam”, prepared in the <gloss target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss> and dated
                    November 15, describes the organization and the assigned duties of the <gloss
                        target="#t_MAAG1">MAAG</gloss>. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, Pentalateral
                    Agreement (130))</p>
            </div>
